transcripts.text: My name is Jolynn Live.  I'm a citizen journalist with Sea Vine News Network.  I'm in Spokane, Washington.  There's a rally here.  It's called Freedom is the Cure.  Spokane citizens are more than ready to open their businesses.  I asked a few citizens why they came to the rally today.
I'm standing up to fight the tyranny that's going on right now with this COVID-19, the actual behind-the-scenes tyranny of it, so my grandkids don't have to fight it.
Do you think it's going to make a difference today?
Well, absolutely.  A lot of people's eyes are opening up all across America right now.  People in every capital right now are having the same rally across the United States.
You're welcome.  And why are you here today?

I'm here to support the theory of common sense.  I mean, it's time for us to get back to work.  The economy has completely disintegrated, and we need to start rebuilding things.  We were on the right track before all this started, and we need to continue down that same path.  And if people are concerned for their own safety and contracting the coronavirus, then they need to practice hygiene and wear a mask.  And if you don't feel that that's good enough, then stay home.  But the rest of everybody needs to get back out and get to work if you so choose to.  And if you don't, then I'm sure that there's protections out there that your employers can't retaliate against you.  You can stay home, the government will back you, but it's common sense.  We need to get back to work.

We don't want our governor telling us we cannot go back to work.  We feel Spokane is a safe place.  It didn't get hit hard.  And we waited for the rise in the fall of the line they're talking about.  And we've waited for this amount of time until May 1st.  And now he extends it longer.  We have a coffee shop and we will be opening Monday completely.  So we will, if they would consider it, we're breaking the law.  But there is actually not a law that we have to stay out of business.  I have a family and I have 11 girls that work for me and they have families.  And we want to continue to make our own money and save our companies.
If you had a word for Governor Inslee, what would it be?

He needs to have some common sense of looking at this side of the mountains in this Washington state is so much different than his side of the state.  And we totally feel for anybody that's caught this or died.  Don't get us wrong, this is horrible.  But what's happening with our businesses is just as horrible, so we can't have them both.  We have to be smart about this and let people go back to work.  Be smart in their workplaces.  We will be smart.  We will have social distancing even though we don't like it, but we will do that.  So we will get our businesses up and running with or without the okay of the government.
You know, I think there's a... Job, teacher, family, your job is essential!
Freedom!  Freedom!  Freedom!  I'm Jolynn Live with C-Vine News Network.  Media for we the people because we are the news now.
